(412, 585, 'Colin', 'creutter@gmail.com', 'http://cqfx.org', '72.175.103.149', '2009-09-27 17:04:08', '2009-09-28 00:04:08', 'I was just talking to somebody last week about why manhole covers are round.  Do they really have square manhole covers there?  Clearly there are communication issues on all levels there.\r\n\r\n--"Can we get some round manhole covers"\r\n-"Why"\r\n--"The square ones keep falling down the hole"\r\n-"But the square ones are easier to make"\r\n\r\n/facepalm', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en-US; rv:1.9.1.3) Gecko/20090824 Firefox/3.5.3 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', 0, 0, ''),
(269, 141, 'Another CLS Applicant', 'lbt940@yahoo.com', '', '75.18.202.181', '2009-02-15 16:11:35', '2009-02-15 23:11:35', '"Intense exotic appeal" and "mystery intrigue?"  These are the types of words and ideas that isolate cultures, rather than bring about meaningful exchange and understanding.  I highly recommend that you take a look at Edward Said''s work on "Orientalism."', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.0; en-US; rv:1.9.0.6) Gecko/2009011913 Firefox/3.0.6', '', 0, 0, ''),
(270, 141, 'Dan', 'dlecocq@mines.edu', 'http://dan.lecocq.us/wordpress/', '24.8.119.217', '2009-02-15 16:27:03', '2009-02-15 23:27:03', 'Thank you for your comment.\n\n<blockquote>"intense exotic appeal" and "mystery intrigue?" these are the types of words and ideas that isolate cultures, rather than bring about meaningful exchange and understanding.</blockquote>\n\nI disagree.  I think that rather than a consistent perspective, it''s a state.  Having now only been to the Middle East once, it''s less mysterious, but without mystery and intrigue (incidentally, I hadn''t caught the typo when posting it), cultural exchange would be seriously stunted.  A world without difference and "exotic appeal" is a dull one, I believe.\n\n<blockquote>i highly recommend that you take a look at edward said''s work on orientalism.</blockquote>\n\nOf course that''s the work for which he''s best known.  The Said book I mentioned in the post was given to me by my cousin in D.C. and so I will likely read it before "Orientalism."', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_6; en-us) AppleWebKit/525.27.1 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/3.2.1 Safari/525.27.1', '', 269, 1, ''),
(304, 115, 'saudikaust', 'rxfaith@gmail.com', '', '62.150.232.68', '2009-03-16 04:26:06', '2009-03-16 11:26:06', 'Any more insight on KAUST?  Jawad, did you have your interview yet?  When did you apply?', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.0.7) Gecko/2009021906 Firefox/3.0.7', '', 0, 0, ''),
(323, 508, 'Andrew Ferguson', 'andrew@fergcorp.com', 'http://andrewferguson.net', '97.122.199.180', '2009-04-26 23:48:19', '2009-04-27 06:48:19', 'Queue Holst: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Holst-_mars.ogg', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.0; en-US) AppleWebKit/525.19 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/1.0.154.59 Safari/525.19', '', 0, 0, ''),
(324, 115, 'nadia', 'rowlingrides@rediff.com', '', '115.241.133.21', '2009-04-27 08:54:33', '2009-04-27 15:54:33', 'Well, they very much have influenced my alternate plans.  As you can guess they still havent scheduled our interviews.  It''s the end of april, so this is very nerve wracking.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 6.0; Windows NT 5.1; SV1)', '', 0, 0, ''),
(325, 115, 'nadia', 'rowlingrides@rediff.com', '', '115.241.133.21', '2009-04-27 08:56:34', '2009-04-27 15:56:34', 'I just hope I hear from them some time soon because I have to travel somewhere, and I don''t want these things to clash.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 6.0; Windows NT 5.1; SV1)', '', 0, 0, ''),
(326, 501, 'CQ', 'creutter@gmail.com', '', '72.175.103.14', '2009-04-28 03:15:51', '2009-04-28 10:15:51', 'Could you add (or whatever it''s called...screen maybe) the pictures together and then render it.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.0.10) Gecko/2009042316 Firefox/3.0.10 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', 0, 0, ''),
(337, 115, 'Dan', 'dlecocq@mines.edu', 'http://dan.lecocq.us/wordpress/', '76.120.21.106', '2009-05-17 15:18:21', '2009-05-17 22:18:21', 'You should email your point of contact with KAUST.  KAUST is in the middle of taking over the reins from IIE in terms of running the actual institution and so there are bound to be some hitches.\n\nWhatever email address got in touch with you to notify you of your interview initially is definitely who you should talk to.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (X11; U; Linux i686; en-US; rv:1.9.0.10) Gecko/2009042523 Ubuntu/9.04 (jaunty) Firefox/3.0.10', '', 336, 1, ''),
