(345, 115, 'waiting', 'rxfaith@gmail.com', '', '78.154.198.43', '2009-05-28 22:59:02', '2009-05-29 05:59:02', 'Mazen, as far as I know you WILL receive a decision.  I believe they are a little overwhelmed with the number of applicants they have, as well as the fact school is starting soon.  When did u apply?', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.0.10) Gecko/2009042315 Firefox/3.0.10', '', 0, 0, ''),
(429, 607, 'Colin', 'creutter@gmail.com', 'http://cqfx.org', '72.175.103.149', '2009-10-07 22:53:57', '2009-10-08 05:53:57', 'It''s beautiful.  By the way, I just read that KAUST has a $10B endowment...!!?! ten billion freaking dollars! I''m sure you knew that already, but it is blowing my mind right now.\r\n\r\nwow', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en-US; rv:1.9.1.3) Gecko/20090824 Firefox/3.5.3 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', 0, 0, ''),
(404, 583, 'Colin', 'creutter@gmail.com', 'http://cqfx.org', '198.202.202.22', '2009-09-24 08:50:34', '2009-09-24 15:50:34', 'Dude, this is the best thing I have read anywhere in the last month. Fascinating.  Hang in there.  I''m sure the inherent difficulties of getting a large institution running compounded by the cultural and security issues are a extremely stressful, but you can navigate this choppy sea.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en-US; rv:1.9.1.3) Gecko/20090824 Firefox/3.5.3 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', 0, 0, ''),
(361, 115, 'mazen', 'mazen1986@yahoo.com', '', '212.138.69.18', '2009-06-27 20:17:15', '2009-06-28 03:17:15', 'Dear all , \r\n\r\nThank you for your response.\r\n\r\nI applied for the KAUST discovery scholarship in January,2009. and I have not heard anything from them. \r\n\r\nHas anyone heard from them yet?\r\n\r\nAnd after which date if we did not get any feedback from them that means we are not accepted?\r\n\r\nWhen will the KAUST interviews start? Because if they started it and we did not anything from them that means where are not accepted .\r\n\r\nRegards,', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.0; en-GB; rv:1.9.0.10) Gecko/2009042316 Firefox/3.0.10', '', 0, 0, ''),
(349, 115, 'Student', 'aabirusabeel@gmail.com', '', '188.49.104.71', '2009-06-06 15:41:13', '2009-06-06 22:41:13', 'I have applied for MS in EE. Got an email recently saying all my documents have been received and my application is forwarded for evaluation. What do I do now? Seems like there will be an interview if I am selected.\r\nAnybody know what''s their GRE requirement? Heard it''s really high.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.0.10) Gecko/2009042316 Firefox/3.0.10', '', 0, 0, ''),
(350, 115, 'Dan', 'dlecocq@mines.edu', 'http://dan.lecocq.us/wordpress/', '67.190.73.115', '2009-06-06 15:45:30', '2009-06-06 22:45:30', 'That just means that they''ve received your submission, and if they''re interested after looking at all applicants, they''ll contact you for interview information.\n\nRegarding the GRE, though they may have changed the policy in subsequent rounds, we did not have to take the GRE in order to get accepted or even apply.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_7; en-us) AppleWebKit/528.16 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/4.0 Safari/528.16', '', 349, 1, ''),
(277, 453, 'Andrew Ferguson', 'andrew@fergcorp.com', 'http://andrewferguson.net', '97.122.192.140', '2009-02-22 00:47:53', '2009-02-22 07:47:53', 'It reminds me a bit of a Piet Mondrian painting...although without the colors. Very well done though.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.0; en-US) AppleWebKit/525.19 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/1.0.154.48 Safari/525.19', '', 0, 0, ''),
(278, 453, 'Dan', 'dlecocq@mines.edu', 'http://dan.lecocq.us/wordpress/', '67.190.160.253', '2009-02-22 09:44:29', '2009-02-22 16:44:29', 'It does a bit, and thanks.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_6; en-us) AppleWebKit/525.27.1 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/3.2.1 Safari/525.27.1', '', 277, 1, ''),
(281, 141, 'Cam', 'camjwill@gmail.com', '', '128.253.56.169', '2009-02-25 18:35:01', '2009-02-26 01:35:01', 'So how did it go? Did you get in?', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.0.5) Gecko/2008120122 Firefox/3.0.5', '', 0, 0, ''),
(282, 141, 'Dan', 'dlecocq@mines.edu', 'http://dan.lecocq.us/wordpress/', '24.8.119.217', '2009-02-25 20:12:52', '2009-02-26 03:12:52', 'We should all find out by "the end of March."  Hopefully sooner, but I''m crossing my fingers.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_6; en-us) AppleWebKit/528.16 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/4.0 Safari/528.16', '', 281, 1, ''),
(419, 585, 'Dan', 'dlecocq@mines.edu', 'http://dan.lecocq.us/wordpress/', '86.51.114.4', '2009-10-01 00:40:00', '2009-10-01 07:40:00', 'I realize that the lip is what makes it stay in place.  The point is, if you lift it up and rotate it, you can drop the cover through.  It''s like taking a window screen off of a window from inside - you detach it, and then rotate it so that its longest dimension is oriented diagonally in the window and pull it through.\n\nThe point is that this maneuver is impossible with a circular manhole cover.  They both need lips, but the fact that by design a circular manhole cover cannot pass through the manhole itself in any orientation is very important.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_8; en-us) AppleWebKit/531.9 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/4.0.3 Safari/531.9', '', 417, 1, ''),
(420, 589, 'Andrew Ferguson', 'andrew@fergcorp.com', 'http://andrewferguson.net', '130.76.32.181', '2009-10-02 09:15:09', '2009-10-02 16:15:09', 'On Windows:\r\nPrintScreen - Captures the entire screen\r\nAlt + PrintScreen - Captures the active window only', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.0.13) Gecko/2009073022 (CK-zz) Firefox/3.0.13', '', 0, 0, ''),
(399, 577, 'Colin', 'creutter@gmail.com', 'http://cqfx.org', '72.175.103.149', '2009-09-20 13:24:19', '2009-09-20 20:24:19', 'Hey, I like the new theme.  Looks good.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en-US; rv:1.9.1.3) Gecko/20090824 Firefox/3.5.3 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', 0, 0, ''),
(402, 579, 'Colin', 'creutter@gmail.com', '', '72.175.103.149', '2009-09-22 13:13:02', '2009-09-22 20:13:02', '47 minutes and counting...', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en-US; rv:1.9.1.3) Gecko/20090824 Firefox/3.5.3 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', 0, 0, ''),
(400, 577, 'Dan', 'dlecocq@mines.edu', 'http://dan.lecocq.us/wordpress/', '86.51.114.4', '2009-09-20 13:31:42', '2009-09-20 20:31:42', 'Hey, thanks! I aim to please. I took an hour to check out my options, and it was down to this and three others, and I thought this was most `me.''', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_8; en-us) AppleWebKit/531.9 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/4.0.3 Safari/531.9', '', 399, 1, ''),
(305, 115, 'Dan', 'dlecocq@mines.edu', 'http://dan.lecocq.us/wordpress/', '138.67.140.103', '2009-03-16 11:37:59', '2009-03-16 18:37:59', 'Think of these interviews as a chance for them to kick the tires, so to speak.  They''ve seen your academic record, but they want to get a feel for what kind of person and student you are.  You might expect to hear questions like, "Why KAUST?" and "What are you interested in researching?"\n\nAlso, I get the impression that these are also to gauge applicants'' English skills.  Some places have problems with students paying other students to take their TOEFL exam for them.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_6; en-us) AppleWebKit/528.16 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/4.0 Safari/528.16', '', 304, 1, ''),
(292, 141, 'Mary Kate G.', 'mail2greengables@afo.net', '', '62.215.222.99', '2009-03-03 12:21:23', '2009-03-03 19:21:23', 'Sitting a few yards from the Persian...uh...Arabian Gulf here in Kuwait, =) I found your post about the Critical Language Scholarship fascinating. As a former White House Intern, and with my Masters in Political Science just conferred in December 2008, I also applied to the Critical Language Scholarship program for Arabic this summer. May the best man...uh...person, win, =) although I must say your essays are far more entertaining and well-written than my own. Keep us posted when you hear back on the CLS! Best of luck!', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 7.0; Windows NT 6.0; SLCC1; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; Media Center PC 5.0; .NET CLR 3.0.04506)', '', 0, 0, ''),
(293, 141, 'Frank', 'zclin@uchicago.edu', 'http://giveyourdogafrank.blogspot.com', '128.135.219.91', '2009-03-04 19:27:03', '2009-03-05 02:27:03', 'I came across your site after googling "critical language scholarship."  This post is the fourth link to come up.  I applied this year as well for the Intermediate Arabic program.  I heard decisions are supposed to  be handed down soon?', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.0; en-US) AppleWebKit/525.19 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/1.0.154.48 Safari/525.19', '', 0, 0, ''),
(413, 585, 'Dan', 'dlecocq@mines.edu', 'http://dan.lecocq.us/wordpress/', '86.51.114.4', '2009-09-27 22:14:21', '2009-09-28 05:14:21', 'Yep.  Definitely have square manhole covers.  Not all of them are, but the fact that square ones are even manufactured in the first place makes no sense to me.  I can''t imagine any specialized need for square ones.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_8; en-us) AppleWebKit/531.9 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/4.0.3 Safari/531.9', '', 0, 1, ''),
(496, 672, 'Colin', 'creutter@gmail.com', 'http://cqfx.org', '72.175.103.149', '2009-10-30 14:30:55', '2009-10-30 21:30:55', 'Pictures! Ideally some kind of stereotypical daily picture video with this as the music: http://www.last.fm/music/Carly+Comando/_/Everyday?autostart\r\n\r\nAnd you should have a different part of KAUST in the background for everyday.\r\n\r\nExample: http://www.snotr.com/video/738', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en-US; rv:1.9.1.4) Gecko/20091016 Firefox/3.5.4 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', 0, 0, ''),
(417, 585, 'Jeff', 'jeff@jeff.com', '', '140.241.0.20', '2009-09-30 12:40:57', '2009-09-30 19:40:57', 'Well, not all manhole covers are simply "square."  They have two squares - one is smaller than the outer (the one that rests on the ground) and the one that you see over the top.\r\n\r\nSo essientially it has a "lip," which is much easier to make than a circle cover and still doesn''t fall through.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en-US; rv:1.9.1.3) Gecko/20090824 Firefox/3.5.3 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', 0, 0, ''),
(296, 141, 'Adam', 'asmith0929@gmail.com', '', '24.175.130.15', '2009-03-07 10:18:58', '2009-03-07 17:18:58', 'I just got my congrats email yesterday! I am so excited!', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; ar; rv:1.9.0.7) Gecko/2009021906 Firefox/3.0.7', '', 0, 0, ''),
(301, 115, 'jawad', 'jawad12ca@hotmail.com', '', '141.217.174.187', '2009-03-11 08:55:40', '2009-03-11 15:55:40', 'Thanks for your insights, I have an interview with KAUST sometime soon. Could you please tell me the type of questions and how the interview went?\r\n', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 7.0; Windows NT 5.1; .NET CLR 1.1.4322; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 3.0.04506.648; InfoPath.2)', '', 0, 0, ''),
(321, 501, 'CQ', 'creutter@gmail.com', 'http://cq-fx.net', '72.175.103.14', '2009-04-26 15:50:29', '2009-04-26 22:50:29', 'That is pretty cool.\r\n\r\nThere is a project at sourceforge for providing real time cloud maps.\r\n(http://xplanet.sourceforge.net/clouds.php)', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.0.9) Gecko/2009040821 Firefox/3.0.9 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', 0, 0, ''),
(322, 501, 'Dan', 'dlecocq@mines.edu', 'http://dan.lecocq.us/wordpress/', '24.8.119.217', '2009-04-26 22:09:14', '2009-04-27 05:09:14', 'Nice.  I did a quick render with one of their pictures, but was disappointed with how lackluster it looked without color.  But I did find some links from there that worked out pretty well for textures for other planets (see most recent post).', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (X11; U; Linux i686; en-US; rv:1.9.0.9) Gecko/2009042113 Ubuntu/9.04 (jaunty) Firefox/3.0.9', '', 321, 1, ''),
(313, 115, 'nadia', 'rowlingrides@rediff.com', '', '115.241.184.248', '2009-04-08 21:28:36', '2009-04-09 04:28:36', 'Hello, please give me any new input about the interviews.  I am a finalist too.  Is it true they are going to further shortlist?', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 6.0; Windows NT 5.1; SV1)', '', 0, 0, ''),
(314, 495, 'Matt Matteson', 'Matt@dlzip.com', 'http://MattMatteson.com', '71.56.221.110', '2009-04-10 00:20:48', '2009-04-10 07:20:48', 'I''m glad you put this all together. \r\n\r\nTo think all of the Pixar videos done in this fashion; cool.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_6; en-us) AppleWebKit/528.16 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/4.0 Safari/528.16', '', 0, 0, ''),
(315, 115, 'Dan', 'dlecocq@mines.edu', 'http://dan.lecocq.us/wordpress/', '138.67.143.239', '2009-04-10 11:40:56', '2009-04-10 18:40:56', 'I know a couple of people who are still waiting on interviews, and I''d expect that they wouldn''t make announcements until all the interviews are in.  Not all people interviewed in my round were accepted (though many were), but I''m not entirely sure how this and subsequent rounds will play out.  Best of luck, though, and feel free to post as you get information!', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_6; en-us) AppleWebKit/528.16 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/4.0 Safari/528.16', '', 313, 1, ''),
(316, 495, 'Dan', 'dlecocq@mines.edu', 'http://dan.lecocq.us/wordpress/', '138.67.143.239', '2009-04-10 11:44:40', '2009-04-10 18:44:40', 'Once I get a few more features implemented (object refraction, octrees, fixed lathe normals, and world rotation / translation), I''m going to make a clip (I''m thinking about 1-2 minutes in HD) that''s a little more involved, and really shows some of the capabilities.  I do have a clip with reflections, which, when they work, are pretty realistic, but there are still some residual artifacts from erroneous normals.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_6; en-us) AppleWebKit/528.16 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/4.0 Safari/528.16', '', 314, 1, ''),
(327, 115, 'Masters', 'rxfaith@gmail.com', '', '78.89.43.65', '2009-04-30 02:00:05', '2009-04-30 09:00:05', 'Applied for the masters program through the fellowship.  Anyone else here in the same boat?  Hoping to hear back any day now.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.0.8) Gecko/2009032608 Firefox/3.0.8', '', 0, 0, ''),
(318, 115, 'nadia', 'rowlingrides@rediff.com', '', '115.241.229.29', '2009-04-13 20:34:50', '2009-04-14 03:34:50', 'They really have delayed the interview schedules this time.  It''s mid April and there is no new update.  I wonder what''s going on.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 6.0; Windows NT 5.1; SV1)', '', 0, 0, ''),
(319, 141, 'Sharon Endelman', 'endelfam@aol.com', '', '205.188.116.71', '2009-04-14 17:53:49', '2009-04-15 00:53:49', 'My son just got his acceptance for Amman, likely in the advanced Arabic program. He''s had three years of Arabic and studied in Cairo last fall. He had been on the alternate list, but the scholarship came through last week.  Maybe he''ll see you there. He''s from Emory.  Congrats!', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 7.0; AOL 9.1; AOLBuild 4334.5006; Windows NT 6.0; WOW64; SLCC1; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 3.0.04506; Media Center PC 5.0)', '', 0, 0, ''),
(320, 115, 'Dan', 'dlecocq@mines.edu', 'http://dan.lecocq.us/wordpress/', '24.8.119.217', '2009-04-14 23:17:43', '2009-04-15 06:17:43', 'With the school opening in September of this year, I''m sure the administration has a lot on its plate beyond the interviews.  That said, I''m sure they will make provisions, and hopefully they''ll be in time to not influence your alternate plans.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_6; en-us) AppleWebKit/528.16 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/4.0 Safari/528.16', '', 318, 1, ''),
(351, 115, 'Student', 'aabirusabeel@gmail.com', '', '188.50.62.20', '2009-06-07 00:56:21', '2009-06-07 07:56:21', 'GRE wasn''t required for Discovery Scholarship. I have applied for KAUST Fellowship as I am joining this fall. They said they were looking for GRE score 770 or more in quantitative section. Don''t know whether they have changed it later.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.0.10) Gecko/2009042316 Firefox/3.0.10', '', 0, 0, ''),
(352, 115, 'waiting', 'rxfaith@gmail.com', '', '62.150.107.145', '2009-06-08 11:38:12', '2009-06-08 18:38:12', 'Student, where did you get your info for on the GRE requirements?', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.0.10) Gecko/2009042315 Firefox/3.0.10', '', 0, 0, ''),
(354, 115, 'Dan', 'dlecocq@mines.edu', 'http://dan.lecocq.us/wordpress/', '67.190.73.115', '2009-06-08 20:55:12', '2009-06-09 03:55:12', 'Discovery Scholarship / Fellowship / etc. applications are done in cycles.  I believe they''ve begun a fourth cycle, but I''m not certain.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_7; en-us) AppleWebKit/528.16 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/4.0 Safari/528.16', '', 353, 1, ''),
(356, 115, 'Student', 'aabirusabeel@gmail.com', '', '188.52.111.101', '2009-06-10 09:04:16', '2009-06-10 16:04:16', 'A friend of mine had emailed them enquiring about GRE requirements.\r\n\r\nI had applied in Jan, but my GRE scores were sent last month. Another friend was saying they were still accepting applications until June 10.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.0.10) Gecko/2009042316 Firefox/3.0.10', '', 0, 0, ''),
(430, 107, 'Empirical Mathematics', '', 'http://dan.lecocq.us/wordpress/2009/10/08/empirical-mathematics/', '74.50.10.10', '2009-10-08 00:46:16', '2009-10-08 07:46:16', '[...] an analytical solution I&#8217;ve reached and occasionally, to reach an analytical result. At one point, I was playing around with the time complexity of heapsort, and I came across a statement about [...]', 0, '1', 'The Incutio XML-RPC PHP Library -- WordPress/2.8.4', 'pingback', 0, 0, ''),
(310, 115, 'mubashir', 'mubashir_nustian@yahoo.co.uk', '', '203.175.69.210', '2009-03-24 14:17:12', '2009-03-24 21:17:12', 'Hi guys, nice to see finalists for KAUST interviews as i''m also one of the finalist and asked to give my interview in Dubai as i''m from Pakistan.\r\nI will also like to hear about interviews...\r\n\r\nbest regards', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.0.5) Gecko/2008120122 Firefox/3.0.5', '', 0, 0, ''),
(816, 839, 'dan.lecocq', 'dan.lecocq@kaust.edu.sa', 'http://dan.lecocq.us/wordpress', '86.51.114.108', '2010-05-19 21:25:12', '2010-05-20 04:25:12', 'Right now I have a headless Ubuntu desktop that I use for offsite backups and storage and then my trusty MacBook.  Seriously, it''s practically my sidekick - it goes everywhere with me.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_8; en-US) AppleWebKit/533.4 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/5.0.375.29 Safari/533.4', '', 815, 2, ''),
(422, 589, 'Joe Sixpack', 'joesixpack@iamtotallyawesome.com', 'http://www.sarahpac.com/', '72.175.103.149', '2009-10-02 12:19:41', '2009-10-02 19:19:41', 'yeah, thank fur helpin me with my totaly awesum gateway runing Windoz 2000.  Wat do u have aganst mainstreat America (Go USA!!!) you elitis pig?!', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en-US; rv:1.9.1.3) Gecko/20090824 Firefox/3.5.3 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', 0, 0, ''),
(423, 589, 'Joe Sixpack', 'joesixpack@iamtotallyawesome.com', 'http://www.sarahpac.com/', '72.175.103.149', '2009-10-02 12:27:56', '2009-10-02 19:27:56', 'btw, i used andrews tip to capture my screan.\r\n\r\nhttp://ozspeak.com/wp-content/uploads/2008/11/too_many_toolbars.jpg', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en-US; rv:1.9.1.3) Gecko/20090824 Firefox/3.5.3 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', 0, 0, ''),
(425, 585, 'Wess', 'sbinayat@gmail.com', '', '121.52.152.88', '2009-10-05 03:59:57', '2009-10-05 10:59:57', '1. After reading all this I get an impression,KAUST isn''t all the attractive rather gives a scary picture. Do you expect things taking a more professional approach in near future?\r\n2. Whats the amount of monthly stipend for a PhD?\r\n3. How good is the housing if dependants accompany you for your PhD?', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 6.0; Windows NT 5.1; SV1)', '', 0, 0, ''),
(426, 585, 'Dan', 'dlecocq@mines.edu', 'http://dan.lecocq.us/wordpress/', '86.51.114.4', '2009-10-05 04:11:40', '2009-10-05 11:11:40', '1. As they say here, إن شاء الله.  It''s hard to say, but if they would like to continue to attract students to a country like KSA, there will need to be changes made.\r\n2. For future classes, it''s unknown, and there has been some confusion even now about the amount.  They''ve asked us to not widely discuss the value of compensation, however.\r\n3. It varies widely - some families have had no problems and others have had just as many as the students.  Perhaps with some time, one might expect the situation to improve.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_8; en-us) AppleWebKit/531.9 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/4.0.3 Safari/531.9', '', 0, 1, ''),
(815, 839, 'Colin', 'creutter@gmail.com', 'http://cqfx.org', '69.144.241.206', '2010-05-19 20:32:01', '2010-05-20 03:32:01', 'So do you use a laptop or do you have a desktop?\r\n\r\nI played Modern Warfare 2 during last Christmas break and one time the host was somebody using a netbook. It was kind of a waste of time but really fun. I met somebody who went by, "Conan the Librarian" and claimed that he was actually a librarian named Conan.\r\n\r\nhttp://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mZHoHaAYHq8', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en-US) AppleWebKit/532.5 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/4.1.249.1064 Safari/532.5', '', 0, 0, ''),
(549, 766, 'dan.lecocq', 'dan.lecocq@kaust.edu.sa', 'http://dan.lecocq.us/wordpress', '86.51.114.110', '2009-12-08 13:49:54', '2009-12-08 20:49:54', 'Yeah, it''s like modern locks - not strong, but just enough inconvenience to keep people out for the most part.  The formatting, obfuscation and so forth are really the only deterrents.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_8; en-us) AppleWebKit/531.21.8 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/4.0.4 Safari/531.21.10', '', 546, 2, ''),
(557, 141, 'c', 'cdejes@gmail.com', '', '64.132.0.243', '2009-12-15 14:33:27', '2009-12-15 21:33:27', 'Your essays are too long. Max wording is 300', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 6.0; Windows NT 5.1; SV1; InfoPath.1; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 3.0.4506.2152; .NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', 0, 0, '');
INSERT INTO `wp_comments` (`comment_ID`, `comment_post_ID`, `comment_author`, `comment_author_email`, `comment_author_url`, `comment_author_IP`, `comment_date`, `comment_date_gmt`, `comment_content`, `comment_karma`, `comment_approved`, `comment_agent`, `comment_type`, `comment_parent`, `user_id`, `comment_pid_ID`) VALUES
(530, 740, 'Colin', 'creutter@gmail.com', 'http://cqfx.org', '174.44.226.224', '2009-11-29 17:16:38', '2009-11-30 00:16:38', 'The campus still looks beautiful even when partially submerged.  You must be getting quite a bit of traffic to this post.  I found some of your photos on another site: http://www.ihudaif.com/2009/11/29/rain-disaster-reaches-kaust/', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en-US; rv:1.9.1.4) Gecko/20091016 Firefox/3.5.4 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', 0, 0, ''),
(531, 740, 'dan.lecocq', 'dan.lecocq@kaust.edu.sa', 'http://dan.lecocq.us/wordpress', '86.51.114.110', '2009-11-29 23:53:46', '2009-11-30 06:53:46', 'Yeah, I hadn''t checked up on it - still waiting for internet access in my home, but there''s been a fair amount, I guess.  There have been some ominous clouds hanging about lately - I don''t know if we''re quite ready for round two.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_8; en-us) AppleWebKit/531.9 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/4.0.3 Safari/531.9', '', 530, 2, ''),
(532, 2, 'Mark J.', 'mjanzer@ljaengineering.com', 'http://www.ljaengineering.com', '66.162.218.34', '2009-11-30 09:05:22', '2009-11-30 16:05:22', 'Any follow-up on the flooding at KAUST? The low area in front of the buildings (the second picture of your posting), is designed as a detention pond. All the main campus roof drainage and plazas drain to it, by design.\r\n\r\nNice blog.\r\n\r\nRegards,', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 7.0; Windows NT 5.1; .NET CLR 1.1.4322; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 3.0.04506.30; InfoPath.1; .NET CLR 3.0.04506.648; .NET CLR 3.0.4506.2152; .NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', 0, 0, ''),
(533, 2, 'dan.lecocq', 'dan.lecocq@kaust.edu.sa', 'http://dan.lecocq.us/wordpress', '86.51.114.110', '2009-11-30 09:13:09', '2009-11-30 16:13:09', 'There are still some major services out, mostly in IT.  For isolated parts of campus there is no internet or telephone service (my apartment building is the notable example in my mind, of course).  Outside of that, the biggest concern will be the mold that will arrive in force, and dealing with the damage to roofs, ceilings, etc.  And it''s not like we didn''t have a mold problem to begin with.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_8; en-us) AppleWebKit/531.9 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/4.0.3 Safari/531.9', '', 532, 2, ''),
(534, 746, 'Andrew Ferguson', 'andrew@fergcorp.com', 'http://andrewferguson.net', '130.76.32.15', '2009-11-30 15:09:12', '2009-11-30 22:09:12', 'Dan, I''m pretty sure you are having too much fun. I''m going to need you to tone it down a bit ;)', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.0.15) Gecko/2009101601 (CK-zz) Firefox/3.0.15', '', 0, 0, ''),
(695, 740, 'dan.lecocq', 'dan.lecocq@kaust.edu.sa', 'http://dan.lecocq.us/wordpress', '86.51.114.108', '2010-01-16 21:28:53', '2010-01-17 04:28:53', 'I did go back to KAUST after winter break. I''m still uncertain about how many students did not return - it''s still all rumor at this point.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_8; en-US) AppleWebKit/532.5 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/4.0.249.49 Safari/532.5', '', 694, 2, ''),
(536, 758, 'Mom', 'lecocq_w_hope@hotmail.com', '', '67.173.252.163', '2009-11-30 18:48:41', '2009-12-01 01:48:41', 'Dan,\r\n  That gave me goose bumps! Fantastic! Amazing!\r\nI will watch it over and over again! Definitely far out!', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.0; en-US; rv:1.9.1.5) Gecko/20091102 Firefox/3.5.5 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', 0, 0, ''),
(539, 746, 'dan.lecocq', 'dan.lecocq@kaust.edu.sa', 'http://dan.lecocq.us/wordpress', '86.51.114.110', '2009-12-02 02:24:27', '2009-12-02 09:24:27', 'I used a framework called CGLX (developed at UCSD) as the windowing system for the tiled display.  Each of their setups has a head node where the code is run, and then geometry is split up to be rendered among the various display nodes.  Each of those computers is responsible for running a few displays.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_8; en-us) AppleWebKit/531.21.8 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/4.0.4 Safari/531.21.10', '', 538, 2, ''),
(564, 141, 'dan.lecocq', 'dan.lecocq@kaust.edu.sa', 'http://dan.lecocq.us/wordpress', '133.22.41.130', '2009-12-19 00:01:01', '2009-12-19 07:01:01', 'When I applied, though this may have changed, the per-essay limit was 500 words.  I thought I hit that target, but in my experience, no essay reader counts words.  I''d say that 95% of the time, they stop reading when they think they''ve read about the limit.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_8; en-US) AppleWebKit/532.5 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/4.0.249.30 Safari/532.5', '', 557, 2, ''),
(642, 787, 'Jan', 'jan@poeschko.com', 'http://www.poeschko.com', '80.123.2.143', '2010-01-02 14:20:14', '2010-01-02 21:20:14', 'Thank you for this report, looks awesome! Are there any plans of releasing webGLot to the public? I would be very much interested in a (web/JavaScript) library capable of plotting 3-D functions...', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_8; de-de) AppleWebKit/531.21.8 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/4.0.4 Safari/531.21.10', '', 0, 0, ''),
(545, 762, 'Autokey | Andrew Ferguson', '', 'http://andrewferguson.net/2009/12/04/autokey/', '69.89.31.97', '2009-12-04 19:09:02', '2009-12-05 02:09:02', '[...] here, you might want to subscribe to the RSS feed or email list for updates on this topic.On the recommendation of my friend Dan, I&#8217;m going to try to do some of these programming puzzles from time to time. I&#8217;m also [...]', 0, '1', 'The Incutio XML-RPC PHP Library -- WordPress/2.8.6', 'pingback', 0, 0, ''),
(546, 766, 'Matt Matteson', 'matt@dlzip.com', 'http://www.MattMatteson.com', '67.176.2.113', '2009-12-07 00:35:25', '2009-12-07 07:35:25', 'Thanks for the puzzle. \r\n\r\nsOlvEdIt - Encrypted just means obscured. \r\n\r\nI wish I knew all the sites I create an account for at least are doing this though...', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_6_2; en-us) AppleWebKit/531.21.8 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/4.0.4 Safari/531.21.10', '', 0, 0, ''),
(579, 784, 'John Brown', 'wxguy7@gmail.com', 'http://ruc.noaa.gov/amb/', '70.167.117.89', '2009-12-23 19:38:16', '2009-12-24 02:38:16', 'Last paragraph absolutely true for me.  Yet, it is SO HARD to let go and do smthg else for a while.\r\n\r\nWe consider it a good day when we find a bug.  The more we find, the better day it is.  But, for every 3 bugs we find, we introduce a new one.  So, it seems there are always more out there waiting to be discovered....', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.1.5) Gecko/20091102 Firefox/3.5.5', '', 0, 0, ''),
(550, 740, 'aldrin quilalang', 'aldrinquilalang@aol.com', '', '86.51.114.110', '2009-12-08 22:36:19', '2009-12-09 05:36:19', 'we, the officers and firefighters of KAUST are always here to give you our best efforts to render our services in all of your emergencies. thank you and may GOD bless us all.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_6; en-us) AppleWebKit/525.27.1 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/3.2.1 Safari/525.27.1', '', 0, 0, ''),
(551, 746, 'Murad', 'mmourad211@hotmail.com', '', '212.119.70.62', '2009-12-09 06:01:06', '2009-12-09 13:01:06', 'Nice pictures... But it is good to indicate the real application... Good luck', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 7.0; Windows NT 5.1; .NET CLR 1.1.4322; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; OfficeLiveConnector.1.3; OfficeLivePatch.0.0)', '', 0, 0, ''),
(581, 787, 'Matt Matteson', 'matt@dlzip.com', 'http://www.MattMatteson.com', '67.176.2.113', '2009-12-25 00:19:23', '2009-12-25 07:19:23', 'Thanks for the sneak peak. How does the frame rate compare to OpenGLot?\r\n\r\nGo ninja go!', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_6_2; en-us) AppleWebKit/531.21.8 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/4.0.4 Safari/531.21.10', '', 0, 0, ''),
(877, 872, 'Berk Geveci', 'berk.geveci@kitware.com', '', '66.194.253.20', '2010-07-14 12:35:51', '2010-07-14 19:35:51', 'Modules rock. I use them everyday when developing VTK/ParaView :-)', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_6_4; en-us) AppleWebKit/533.16 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/5.0 Safari/533.16', '', 0, 0, ''),
(878, 872, 'dan.lecocq', 'dan.lecocq@kaust.edu.sa', 'http://dan.lecocq.us/wordpress', '129.34.20.23', '2010-07-14 12:44:51', '2010-07-14 19:44:51', 'I''m glad to know that it sees real-world use outside of campus.  And at Kitware, no less!', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_8; en-US) AppleWebKit/533.4 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/5.0.375.86 Safari/533.4', '', 877, 2, ''),
(699, 740, 'sari', 'sari.abuljadayel@hotmail.com', '', '188.249.170.146', '2010-01-25 22:58:31', '2010-01-26 05:58:31', 'so u have any idea if anyone has been compensated for their losses and were they paid for justly? cos my car got damaged in the flood and i was wondering how everyone else got compensated... thnx', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 8.0; Windows NT 5.1; Trident/4.0; GTB6.3)', '', 0, 0, ''),
(765, 2, 'Colin', 'creutter@gmail.com', 'http://cqfx.org', '174.44.223.198', '2010-03-26 15:29:07', '2010-03-26 22:29:07', 'It''s neat someone who helped design the infrastructure found your blog. I have been missing your posts lately. Hopefully everything is going okay.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en-US; rv:1.9.2.2) Gecko/20100316 Firefox/3.6.2', '', 0, 0, ''),
(572, 778, 'Ismail Hameduddin', 'ismail_hameduddin@hotmail.com', '', '173.30.155.230', '2009-12-20 20:13:45', '2009-12-21 03:13:45', 'Hilarious.', 0, '1', 'Opera/9.80 (Windows NT 5.1; U; en) Presto/2.2.15 Version/10.10', '', 0, 0, ''),
(829, 705, 'RSAO', 'rallendes@utalca.cl', '', '200.91.26.1', '2010-06-07 11:40:30', '2010-06-07 18:40:30', 'Hey... been trying to get some pretty pictures following your comments, but cant get vtk to do any type of nice rendering... did you have to do any other sort of twicking to the datasets? I''ve downloaded them from the volume library, converted them to raw and added the header exactly as you post it... can you point out the points used for the transfer funcitions? perhaps show a bit of the code?\r\n\r\nthanks alot', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-GB; rv:1.9.2.3) Gecko/20100401 Firefox/3.6.3', '', 0, 0, ''),
(575, 784, 'Roni Choudhury', 'aichoudh@gmail.com', '', '155.98.20.184', '2009-12-22 12:14:06', '2009-12-22 19:14:06', 'What was the bug?', 0, '1', 'Opera/9.80 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X; U; en) Presto/2.2.15 Version/10.00', '', 0, 0, ''),
(576, 784, 'dan.lecocq', 'dan.lecocq@kaust.edu.sa', 'http://dan.lecocq.us/wordpress', '220.254.29.134', '2009-12-22 16:01:09', '2009-12-22 23:01:09', 'I was trying to display a screen-filling quad, and apparently WebGL (and OpenGL ES 2) doesn''t support GL_QUADS, but switching to GL_TRIANGLE_STRIP seems to have solved, though I''m only getting one of the triangles that way.\n\nWhat happens when you try to render a quad is a that a single pixel is drawn, and it appears to be on the interior of the primitive, but it''s hard to tell.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_8; en-US) AppleWebKit/532.5 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/4.0.249.30 Safari/532.5', '', 575, 2, ''),
(582, 787, 'dan.lecocq', 'dan.lecocq@kaust.edu.sa', 'http://dan.lecocq.us/wordpress', '220.254.29.134', '2009-12-25 02:42:26', '2009-12-25 09:42:26', 'It''s not quite as good as with OpenGLot.  For equivalent primitives, OpenGLot gets about 300 fps where WebGL gets 60-90.  Still, it''s real-time.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_8; en-US) AppleWebKit/532.5 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/4.0.249.43 Safari/532.5', '', 581, 2, ''),
(766, 571, 'dan.lecocq', 'dan.lecocq@kaust.edu.sa', 'http://dan.lecocq.us/wordpress', '98.218.229.143', '2010-03-30 12:23:06', '2010-03-30 19:23:06', 'Perhaps this is not the best time to reply - I''m away from KAUST for a week and enjoying the US right now.  That might color my thoughts on the subject.\n\nIt''s not horrible.  There are a lot of things going for it that may take effect in the next couple of years.  Currently, we are very happy that the breach is now open six days a week, but only during the day.  And we now have an operational movie theater that is open two nights per week.\n\nThat said, depending on your department, you may have access to state of the art equipment now, or you may not for quite a long time.  Computer science and applied mathematics programs have good access to equipment (especially in visualization and high-performance computing).  Most other departments are not so lucky - marine scientists lack much of even the most basic gear, and other majors don''t have labs yet.\n\nFor all its flaws, I''ve started to make it my home, and the people are generally pretty fantastic.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_8; en-US) AppleWebKit/532.9 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/5.0.307.11 Safari/532.9', '', 764, 2, ''),
(519, 687, 'dan.lecocq', 'dan.lecocq@kaust.edu.sa', 'http://dan.lecocq.us/wordpress', '86.51.114.110', '2009-11-10 22:32:16', '2009-11-11 05:32:16', 'I tried to check out skippy''s website, but it''s blocked and I don''t have a VPN set up yet (or Tor for that matter).\n\nIn that same vein, an Arab-language newspaper ripped off a student''s blog (supposedly translating word for word - again I don''t know about this because google translate is blocked here, too).\n\nNewspaper: http://www.alyaum.com/issue/article.php?IN=13268&amp;I=708121\nBlog: http://saudiaggie.blogspot.com/2009/10/elections.html', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_8; en-us) AppleWebKit/531.9 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/4.0.3 Safari/531.9', '', 517, 2, ''),
(516, 687, 'Colin', 'creutter@gmail.com', 'http://cqfx.org', '174.44.226.224', '2009-11-10 12:27:15', '2009-11-10 19:27:15', 'There is an article about KAUST in the latest Physics Today. \r\n\r\nhttp://ptonline.aip.org/journals/doc/PHTOAD-ft/vol_62/iss_11/24_1.shtml\r\nPDF: http://link.aip.org/link/PHTOAD/v62/i11/p24/s1/pdf', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en-US; rv:1.9.1.4) Gecko/20091016 Firefox/3.5.4 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', 0, 0, ''),
(492, 185, 'Play', '', 'http://dan.lecocq.us/wordpress/2009/10/25/play/', '74.50.10.10', '2009-10-25 08:49:25', '2009-10-25 15:49:25', '[...] mentioned Luis von Ahn before (incidentally he&#8217;s the man behind CAPTCHAs &#8211; the distorted text websites sometimes ask [...]', 0, '1', 'The Incutio XML-RPC PHP Library -- WordPress/2.8.5', 'pingback', 0, 0, ''),
(517, 687, 'Colin', 'creutter@gmail.com', 'http://cqfx.org', '174.44.226.224', '2009-11-10 12:35:46', '2009-11-10 19:35:46', 'It looks like the photos in the article came from this guy: http://skippy.net/\r\n\r\nIt is interesting to see them use a photo from Flickr that are licensed under creative commons.\r\n\r\nhttp://www.flickr.com/photos/skippy/3958239283/in/set-72157622340321297/', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en-US; rv:1.9.1.4) Gecko/20091016 Firefox/3.5.4 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', 0, 0, ''),
(511, 649, 'Colin', 'creutter@gmail.com', 'http://cqfx.org', '72.175.103.149', '2009-11-03 17:32:13', '2009-11-04 00:32:13', 'http://blag.xkcd.com/2009/11/02/notes/', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en-US; rv:1.9.1.4) Gecko/20091016 Firefox/3.5.4 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', 0, 0, ''),
(512, 649, 'dan.lecocq', 'dan.lecocq@kaust.edu.sa', 'http://dan.lecocq.us/wordpress', '86.51.114.110', '2009-11-03 21:53:36', '2009-11-04 04:53:36', 'I actually thought immediately of that book when I saw that comic.  Glad to know I''m in good company!', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_8; en-us) AppleWebKit/531.9 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/4.0.3 Safari/531.9', '', 0, 2, ''),
(694, 740, 'Christian', 'claudel@eecs.berkeley.edu', '', '98.207.248.23', '2010-01-16 18:07:20', '2010-01-17 01:07:20', 'Nice blog!\r\n\r\nDid you go back to Kaust after the winter break? Do you have anything new about the students that didn''t want to go back to Kaust after the winter break?', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.1.7) Gecko/20091221 Firefox/3.5.7 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', 0, 0, ''),
(645, 787, 'dan.lecocq', 'dan.lecocq@kaust.edu.sa', 'http://dan.lecocq.us/wordpress', '86.51.114.108', '2010-01-02 21:40:36', '2010-01-03 04:40:36', 'Yes.  I have every intention of making this project open source, but as I developed it while going to school here, I will need KAUST''s permission to do so.  I don''t anticipate that this will be a problem, but I will have to wait until then.  I have prepared a release - I''m just waiting on approval.\n\nThanks for the interest!', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_8; en-US) AppleWebKit/532.5 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/4.0.249.43 Safari/532.5', '', 642, 2, ''),
(974, 883, 'Ismail Hameduddin', 'ismail_hameduddin@hotmail.com', '', '188.48.115.83', '2010-08-02 09:12:30', '2010-08-02 16:12:30', 'Dan, \r\n\r\nI work in nonlinear systems and control and this looks very intriguing. Dynamicists love visualization techniques and I am wondering of maybe extending this to certain aspects of nonautonomous systems as well.\r\n\r\nKeep up the good work.\r\n\r\nIH', 0, '1', 'Opera/9.80 (Windows NT 5.1; U; en) Presto/2.6.30 Version/10.60', '', 0, 0, ''),
(813, 839, 'Colin', 'creutter@gmail.com', 'http://cqfx.org', '69.144.241.206', '2010-05-19 16:18:55', '2010-05-19 23:18:55', 'Half-Life 2 is one of my favorite games. I''ve only played the first few levels of Portal, but it was on PS3.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en-US) AppleWebKit/532.5 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/4.1.249.1064 Safari/532.5', '', 0, 0, ''),
