(561, 758, 'Vero', 'ChristianValarWannaBe@hotmail.com', '', '63.255.31.202', '2009-12-17 07:40:48', '2009-12-17 14:40:48', 'Nicely done; congratulations.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_8; en-us) AppleWebKit/530.19.2 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/4.0.2 Safari/530.19', '', 0, 0, ''),
(565, 746, 'dan.lecocq', 'dan.lecocq@kaust.edu.sa', 'http://dan.lecocq.us/wordpress', '133.22.41.130', '2009-12-19 00:02:56', '2009-12-19 07:02:56', 'Of course.  It''s easy to grow so accustomed to one''s own work and purpose to the point where one assumes everyone is thinking the same things.\n\nI''ll be expanding on this break, and I''ll be providing some better demos and a `getting started'' section.  Thanks for reading!', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_8; en-US) AppleWebKit/532.5 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/4.0.249.30 Safari/532.5', '', 551, 2, ''),
(841, 679, 'Otto Graham', 'otto@grahamcracker.com', '', '99.73.161.13', '2010-06-17 03:08:18', '2010-06-17 10:08:18', 'I stumbled upon this post and thought you might be interested in free software that does something similar to "motion" but is much more sophisticated.  Take a look at http://www.vitamindinc.com ... there''s a free version which will almost certainly work with your camera.  \r\n\r\nVitamind D offers email alerts when certain events happen and you can set rules and filters for events.  Also, the software tries to be smart about what is recognized as an object, thus drastically culling the video review time.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_6_3; en-US) AppleWebKit/533.4 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/5.0.375.70 Safari/533.4', '', 0, 0, ''),
(700, 740, 'dan.lecocq', 'dan.lecocq@kaust.edu.sa', 'http://dan.lecocq.us/wordpress', '86.51.114.108', '2010-01-26 00:06:52', '2010-01-26 07:06:52', 'None of my friends have gotten checks or compensation for their damaged items yet.  A few have submitted claims, but I don''t think KAUST has gotten back to them.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_8; en-US) AppleWebKit/532.5 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/4.0.249.49 Safari/532.5', '', 699, 2, ''),
(891, 874, 'Colin', 'creutter@gmail.com', 'http://cqfx.org', '174.45.70.86', '2010-07-18 21:53:49', '2010-07-19 04:53:49', 'So it turns out that Bozeman has the oldest computer museum in the world. Weird, huh. Also, it seems that they are trying to preserve some historical moment of the Internet with their website: http://www.compustory.com/', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en-US) AppleWebKit/533.4 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/5.0.375.99 Safari/533.4', '', 0, 0, ''),
