(1190, 512, 'Al Haraka', 'alharaka@gmail.com', 'http://alharaka.wordpress.com', '89.211.60.10', '2010-11-14 10:36:52', '2010-11-14 17:36:52', 'Wow.  This is most cool.  I have recently come to accept my OS X reality for the time being, poking my own Linux-loving eye out.  This is a fun little tool that makes LaTeX go a long way.  Thanks for the tip.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.6; en-US; rv:1.9.2.12) Gecko/20101026 Firefox/3.6.12', '', 0, 0, ''),
(982, 883, 'Ian Romanick', 'idr@freedesktop.org', 'http://www.paranormal-entertainment.com/idr/blog/', '24.21.207.78', '2010-08-04 12:22:23', '2010-08-04 19:22:23', 'I saw your presentation at SIGGRAPH, and I was really impressed.  I have spent this entire year rewriting the GLSL compiler in Mesa (used by many open source driver), and I''m really anxious to try WebGLot on the new compiler.  As far as I''m aware, this one of the very, very few "real" WebGL applications.  We''d love to have it in our test suite. :)', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (X11; U; Linux i686; en-US; rv:1.9.1.6) Gecko/20091216 Iceweasel/3.5.6 (like Firefox/3.5.6; Debian-3.5.6-1)', '', 0, 0, ''),
