idth="299" height="300" class="size-medium wp-image-167" /></a>[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_168" align="aligncenter" width="299" caption="We get our memory back when the program is terminated."]<a href="http://dan.lecocq.us/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2008/11/leak-2.png"><img src="http://dan.lecocq.us/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2008/11/leak-2-299x300.png" alt="We get our memory back when the program is terminated." title="Memory Leak" width="299" height="300" class="size-medium wp-image-168" /></a>[/caption]', 'Memory Leak', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '165-revision-2', '', '', '2008-11-24 23:48:07', '2008-11-25 06:48:07', '', 165, 'http://dan.lecocq.us/wordpress/2008/11/24/165-revision-2/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(171, 1, '2008-11-25 02:47:24', '2008-11-25 09:47:24', 'In all the times I''ve used it to fix many messed up programs, I''ve never seen gdb seg fault.', 'Broken gdb', 0, 'I got gdb to seg fault!', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'picture-3', '', '', '2008-11-25 02:47:24', '2008-11-25 09:47:24', '', 165, 'http://dan.lecocq.us/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2008/11/picture-3.png', 0, 'attachment', 'image/png', 0),
