(490, 1, '2009-04-04 21:17:40', '2009-04-05 04:17:40', 'Up to this point, my ray tracer had been limited to rendering spheres and triangles, and, while there''s a lot you can do with these primitives, it''s often more efficient and effective to use a lathe or surface or rotation.  Imagine you''ve got a curve, and you rotate it around some axis, keeping track of the surface it swept out.\n\nAlternatively, imagine ', 'Ray Tracer Feature: Lathes', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '488-revision', '', '', '2009-04-04 21:17:40', '2009-04-05 04:17:40', '', 488, 'http://dan.lecocq.us/wordpress/2009/04/04/488-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
